   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE DIRECTION OF</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE LORD'S MOVE TODAY Scripture Reading: 1 Tim 3:15; Heb 3:12; Matt 16:18; Rev 5:6b; Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:5, 9; Acts 5:42; John 21:15; Eph 4:12; 1 Cor 14:1, 3-5, 12, 23-26, 31; John 15:1, 5, 8a; Eph 3:19; John 3:29-30; Rev 19:7-8; 22:17; 21:1-2, 9b-10; Luke 19:12, 15a; Dan 2:34-35, 44-45; Rev 11:15 OUTLINE Our God is living 1 Tim 3:15; Heb 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Our Lord is moving Matt 16:18.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>And the Spirit is working Rev 5:6b.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>What is the Lord's move today?</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To recover the New Testament priesthood of the gospel Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:5, 9.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To recover the home meetings for feeding the new believers Acts 5:42; John 21:15.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To recover the perfecting of the saints for the work of the New Testament ministry Eph 4:12.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To recover prophesying for the building up of the church as the Body of Christ 1 Cor 14:1, 3-5, 12, 23-26, 31.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The direction of the Lord's move: To build up the organic Body of Christ as the organism of the processed and dispensing God in His divine Trinity for His full expression Eph 4:12; John 15:1, 5, 8a; Eph 3:19.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To prepare the bride as the counterpart of the Bridegroom for the eternal marriage of the redeeming God with His redeemed John 3:29-30; Rev 19:7-8; 22:17; 21:1-2, 9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To bring in the kingdom of God as the spreading of the divine life for God's eternal administration in the fulfillment of His eternal economy Luke 19:12, 15a; Dan 2:34-35, 44-45; Rev 11:15.</S>
   </TEXT>
